---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Capstone Project Platform">
  <main>
    <section class="bg-[#eef4ec]">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 py-12 md:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold">About Us</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-[#435247]">
          The platform is planned as a lightweight showcase for students' capstone projects and learning outcomes related to emerging technologies in teaching and work contexts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-8 px-5 py-10 md:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr] md:px-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">First-Version Aim</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-sm leading-7 text-[#59685d]">
        <p>
          The first version should establish the platform structure before expanding the content. It should make clear where student projects, background information, and maintenance guidance belong.
        </p>
        <p>
          This version avoids login, CMS editing, approval workflow, database backend, and individual student app hosting. The site remains static and maintainable through structured content files.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
